  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training of 180 School of Hope Volunteer Teachers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over 1 year, 180 volunteer supervisors will participate in an initial 3-day course facilitated by experts, comprising of 16 workshops focusing on life skills, rights &amp; knowledge and relationships &amp; wellbeing. Over the year they will embark on independent learning activities, group tasks, complete a reflective journal and will cascade their knowledge and learning to other supervisors and SoH committee members. A follow up 2-day workshop will reflect on learning gains and share skills.</narrative>
  </description>
